Tanzanian Cotton Production May Increase 53% Amid Rising Prices, News Says

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-05-03T08:40:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/tanzanian-cotton-production-may-increase-53-amid-rising-prices-news-says.html
Tanzanian cotton production may jump
53 percent this season as farmers plant more of the crop to
benefit from higher prices, the  Daily News  reported.  Output may rise to 250,000 metric tons from 163,000 tons
last season, the Dar es Salaam-based newspaper said, citing
Marco Mtunga, director general of the Tanzania Cotton Board.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in  Dar es Salaam  via Nairobi at 
440 or  pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  